cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with learning disentangled image representations, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed model uses regularization techniques to encourage disentanglement, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The model also leverages soft target representations to synthesize novel images, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM).
